HEADWORD: Decomposed
<hw>De`com*posed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Separated or broken up; -- said of the crest of birds when the
feathers are divergent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

